### Core Concepts and Definitions

| Term                      | Description                                                                                  |
|---------------------------|----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------|
| **Stack (ADT)**            | A collection that follows the **Last-In, First-Out (LIFO)** principle.                        |
| **Operations on Stack**    | - Check if stack is empty<br>- Push (add) an item<br>- Pop (remove) the most recently added item<br>- Peek (get) the most recently added item without removing it |
| **LIFO Behavior**          | The last item inserted is the first to be removed.                                          |
| **Balanced Braces**        | A string of braces is balanced if every closing brace matches a previously encountered opening brace, and all braces are matched by the end of the string. |
| **Postfix Expression**     | An algebraic expression where operators appear after their operands.                        |
| **Infix Expression**       | Traditional algebraic notation where operators are between operands.                        |
| **Backtracking**           | A strategy to recover from wrong choices by reverting to previous states (nodes).          |

