### Relationship Between Stacks and Recursion

- Stacks naturally model **recursive function calls**.
- Key aspects:
  - Each recursive call corresponds to pushing a new state onto the stack.
  - Backtracking corresponds to popping states off the stack.
  - Termination occurs when no further recursive calls are made.
